<br>
I know that you may scoff at me for this, but recent events have lead me to conclude that what would really help Wizards to be useful in groups would be an O'Keils group enchantment. Hear me out before you push that back button or start writing your flames with one hand at 60 miles per hour.<br>
<br>
We are wizards. Architects of ruin and masters of damage. It only makes sense that our enchantment be something that adheres to this standard. Damage shields should be as much a part of our class as direct damage spells are. I have taken the liberty of planning the progression of these spells with wizard class balance and group usefullness in mind. I believe that if this is brought about wizards will once again be useful in groups, not only at high lvls, but at lower lvls as well. They will become a desireable addition to groups even against the epic mobs in Velious and other places where wizards were nothing but dead weight before.<br>
<br>
The O'keils line could start as it does, the 2 ds at 4th lvl. Move the flickering flame upgrade down to lvl 12 or so. Upgrade the damage to around 12-20 at lvl 20. Give wizards a group version of this spell at lvl 29. At lvl 34 you can give a single version of this spell with about the same damage (maybe a little more) with additional resist bonuses. At lvl 44 give wizards a group version of the previous spell (with the bonuses) and slightly upgraded damage (around 30-40). At lvl 49 give wizards a single version of this spell with a damage upgrade (about 50) and improved resists. At lvl 52 give wizards a group version of this spell. At lvl 54 Wizards get a single version with a strength bonus for tanks in addition to the previous bonuses with a damage upgrade to around 70-80. At lvl 56 wizards get the final and ultimate upgrade to this spell. A group version with improved resist and strength bonuses, damage of around 90-115, and maybe even a slight regen effect. Verant could make the damage output of these spells increase as you gain levels, like with our direct damage spells.<br>
<br>
If you have read this and still don't understand what perfect sense this make then let me put it into these terms. Magicians are useful in groups because of what they do best: summon. Clerics are useful for what they do best: heal, Enchanters are useful for what they do best: enchant, Tanks are useful for what they do best: tank, ect. What wizards do best is deal damage but we are not useful for that reason. Instead Verant seeks to redifine the wizard to a taxi service and make that his priority. I think that this series of enchantments hold true to the core wizard function and will make us again useful for doing what we do best. Deal damage. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umalidorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malidorn</A> at: 6/16/01 1:52:56 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uennyaorcsbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ennya Orcsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/01 11:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A possible Wizard balance solution.</span><hr size=1> I agree but have an interesting idea...<br>
<br>
A twist to the idea would be to lower the damage a bit, and make the DS something that also covers the weapon. That way the extra damage is delt when anyone hits the mob. Make it unresistable, and make that damage add to the wizards agro (well, gotta give something back =) That way we are differenciated from Mages and others with good DSs. We are the masters of Offensive spells, and that change would reflect it.<br>
<br>
Wow, I really like that idea! Then we wait till that last 20% is left and start making the clerics job easier buy smashing the crap out of the MOB with the bigger DD spells. Hmmm...<br>
<br>
&lt;knock&gt; &lt;knock&gt; Hello, Verant, you there? <p>Ennya Orcsbane<BR>
1st Elder of The Tears Of Veeshan<BR>
