Wizardess<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umandosturambar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mandos Turambar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/01 12:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A possible Wizard balance solution.</span><hr size=1> Just dropped in to see the retirement notices, but started browzing...addict to the core am I, I fear.  Such a spell would indeed be a good group addition: it would make us more group friendly.  However, it's simply not the cruise I signed up for.  I started a wizard to be able to do my own damage, plain and simple.  To blow things up; to freeze them; to send them to Hell.   I cannot do that on a sustainable basis except with pipsqueak things that should never attack a 57 wizard anyway (I don't care about soloing, I can do that of course to the extent Kunark allows it).<br>
<br>
Verant's perception is utterly flawed:  They think we do enough damage (Poe said it again).  We do not.  It is simple: mana, mana, mana.  It's the only fix, by whichever of the myriad of ways that have been suggested, that is consistent with what OUR VISION is.  Screw their redefined &quot;Vision&quot;; if I ever play again, it will be a cold day in whatever Hell Norrath has before I give ANYONE but a groupmate, close friend, or guildmate that has a strong need for it, a taxi ride anywhere.  I do NOT want to be redefined.  That is a dishonest and abusive technique of non-customer service.  It fits perfectly with their normal corporate culture and actions.<br>
<br>
<br>
But enough.  I rant, my apologies.   I return to South Felwithe now, to curse old Tarker Blasetoss to his face and die.  The old fraud.<br>
