Asigner of the Hunt<BR>
Wizardess<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usnyine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Snyine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/01 8:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A possible Wizard balance solution.</span><hr size=1> Please forward this idea to Poe if you think it might work as a alternate group enhancement.<br>
<br>
The wizard class pre-expansion was a well balanced class and the original design was balanced. (post beta) <br>
<br>
The overriding problem with the wizard class is that post expansion our class doesn't scale well. Mele has gained increased efficiency and higher damage ratios.<br>
<br>
The original concept of the wizard class was to be the Damage dealers of the game this concept worked well pre expansions. With mob hit points increasing in the new continents a problem was created that VI either overlooked or Ignored the fact that wizards were not given spells with enough mana efficiency/damage ratio to effectively play in the new Lands.<br>
<br>
The following is a list of Balance suggestions for our class:<br>
<br>
1) Wizards are supposed to be masters of Channeling create for us a group buff called &quot;Magic Reflection&quot; the idea is that this spell creates a temporary magic shield where magic attacks are reflected back against there caster at one half value.<br>
<br>
2) Create a temporal spell line Wizards should be masters of Time and Space. We should get a spell that's group related it can be a level 34 spell and what it does is reduce spell cast and recovery time it could start at 5% reduce for Cast and 10% reduction for recast. This could be a temporal Flux Spell line or a single Quest spell (This should be difficult like our brain bite quest) that scales up as we level.<br>
<br>
3) If a temporal Line is considered then how about a Wizard dot/Buff spell. Now I know what your thinking wizards shouldn't dot or buff.. and I agree but this spell doesn't work like a traditional dot or buff how it works is it is designed to stack with the highest dot or buff on a PC or NPC and will extend the length/duration of that spell by 1/3 or 1/3 the idea is that the wizard is able to manipulate the time on the target to extend the spell. A spell of this design will increase a wizards groupability without changing the classes ability to solo.<br>
<br>
4) WIzards need a increased damage mana ratio ..... verdant doesn't want to give it to us for one huge reason the damage efficient needed would unbalance us in the original game zones by a huge margin. What I suggest is either a continent based spell line. We channel the mystical/magical/elemental forces from that continent. Or they make items available for each continent Channeling Crystals that give percentage increases to Spell Damage and percentage increases to Mana efficiency for those zones that we are inefficient for only.<br>
<br>
5) A alternate Idea would be to create a Imbue spell line for the Wizard class. This spell line would allow wizards to Charge up spell effects into either a quest item ( 10 charges max) or channeling crystals one charge each stackable and expendable on cast. This would enable a wizard to pay the mana cost for some spells in advance. Make the items charged in this manner have a greatly reduced cast time. Quest Items that can be charges have the option by the wizard to &quot;Mana Dump&quot; select a number of spell charges to fire in one shot. High Aggro yes will it look kool when the mobs HP go to 0 real fast Hell yes<br>
 <br>
These are just suggestions that I see for making the wizard fall in line to what the original concept was. The Idea of altering the Character concept to fit the game dynamics is poor customer service shows a lack of concern for continuity in game design.<br>
<br>
<br>
Please feel free to comment or expand on my suggestions <br>
<br>
<br>
